I look at my inner STRENGTH as the foundation of survival. 

When I start to feel overwhelmed by stress/anxiety, which is usually triggered by thinking too far ahead or listening to thoughts that haven’t even happened yet. I write down the truth. 

The truth is I am BRAVE. I’m brave enough to face my difficulties. I am WISE. I’m wise enough to acknowledge what doesn’t feel right or authentic. I am LOVING. I’m loving enough to nurture my well-being, so I can love the ones around me more. All of these truths fall under STRENGTH. I have the strength to survive. 🌙#danielricefitness

How are your squats? Are they deep enough? Stand shoulder width apart with your toes slightly turned out. Inhale to embrace your core while you descend. Make sure to break parallel while maintaining a flexed neutral spine position with an external rotation in the knee joints. Exhale, come up while pushing your knees outwards towards your pinky side of the toes.

Core exercises with time under tension! The idea is to see how many reps you can do for each move while completing the circuit without resting in between. Here is my suggestion…first aim for 10 reps for each move to see how it feels. Then work your way up to 15-20 reps for each move. Rest for 60-90 seconds after you complete the whole circuit. Do this for a total of 4 rounds.

On  R e c o v e r y  days…It is so important to have at least 2 days a week of active resting. This can be anything from low impact movements to completely resting. 🚫 No heavy weight lifting. This can include walking, running, stretching, hot yoga and mobility - the list can go on. This will give the body a chance to recover from weight training, making it more likely to improve strength and growth. This is why in my online workout plans I always program recovery days 2x a week! 💪🏽🧘🏻‍♂️

🌙#danielricefitness
